Malaysian Consul General Abu Bakar Mamat arranged a reception for the 10th year anniversary of the establishment of the Malaysian Consulate General in Karachi.Consuls general of Russia, China, Bahrain, Switzerland, Sri Lanka, France, Japan, Korea and Malaysian community residing in Karachi as well as the business fraternity attended the event.Speaking on the occasion, Mamat said, “We are celebrating our 10 years of consulate’s establishment in Karachi and invited our friends to share the joyous occasion with us so as to make it more memorable event”.The consulate themed the reception Satay Vaganza where guests were treated with special serving of popular Malaysian dish Satay.Yahya Polani said that these types of activities help highlight positive image of the city, adding that he liked Malaysian dishes because these were not oily.